PRESIDENT John Magufuli has appointed Adolf Ndunguru the new Deputy Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Finance and Planning (Policy). According to a statement released yesterday by the State House Directorate of Communication, Mr Ndunguru fills the post that has been vacant. Before the appointment, Mr Ndunguru was the Deputy Commissioner for Tanzania Revenue Authority (TRA). Meanwhile, the Head of State has appointed Mr Msafiri Mbibo to fill Mr Ndunguruâ€™s previous post at TRA. Before the appointment, Mr Mbibo was TRA manager for Kilimanjaro Region. The two appointments are with effect from March 31, 2019